<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="383" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">
Males of 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. paya" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" rank="species" species="paya">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">N. paya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. resemble those of 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. leticia" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" rank="species" species="leticia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">N. leticia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. by having an oval tegulum reaching one-third of the cymbium length (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Nopsma leticia sp. nov., male (MPUJ-ENT 0070411). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A, B: 1.5 mm, C, D: 0.7 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566381" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">2C, D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Nopsma paya sp. nov.; A, B, E, F. male holotype; C, D, G. female paratype (IAvH-I 3796). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B Habitus, ventral view. C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, prolateral view. G. External genitalia, ventral view. H. Internal genitalia, dorsal view. Scale bars: A-D: 1.5 mm, E, F: 0.7 mm, G, H: 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: ap = anterior plate, ess = external sclerotization around spiracles, go = genital opening, pp = posterior plate, re = receptaculum." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566383" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">4E, F</figureCitation>
), but can be distinguished by having a straighter embolus with membranous keel restricted to the opening tip (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Drawings of male copulatory bulbs of Colombian Nopsma species. A, B. Nopsma florencia Sanchez-Ruiz, Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo. C, D. Nopsma macagual sp. nov. E, F. Nopsma leticia sp. nov. G, H. Nopsma paya sp. nov. A, C, E, G. Retrolateral view. B, D, F, H. Prolateral view. Scale bars: 0.7 mm. Abbreviations: e = embolus, mk = membranous keel, t = tegulum." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566385" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">6G, H</figureCitation>
) (curved, with membranous keel surrounding the embolus in 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. leticia" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" rank="species" species="leticia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">N. leticia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Drawings of male copulatory bulbs of Colombian Nopsma species. A, B. Nopsma florencia Sanchez-Ruiz, Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo. C, D. Nopsma macagual sp. nov. E, F. Nopsma leticia sp. nov. G, H. Nopsma paya sp. nov. A, C, E, G. Retrolateral view. B, D, F, H. Prolateral view. Scale bars: 0.7 mm. Abbreviations: e = embolus, mk = membranous keel, t = tegulum." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566385" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">6E, F</figureCitation>
). Females differ from those of 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. juchuy" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" rank="species" species="juchuy">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">N. juchuy</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the only other 
<taxonomicName authority="Sánchez-Ruiz, Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo, 2020" authorityName="Sanchez-Ruiz, Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo" authorityYear="2020" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Nopsma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nopsma" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Nopsma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species known by females, by the external genitalia strongly sclerotized around spiracles, with V-shaped margin on posterior plate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Nopsma paya sp. nov.; A, B, E, F. male holotype; C, D, G. female paratype (IAvH-I 3796). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B Habitus, ventral view. C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, prolateral view. G. External genitalia, ventral view. H. Internal genitalia, dorsal view. Scale bars: A-D: 1.5 mm, E, F: 0.7 mm, G, H: 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: ap = anterior plate, ess = external sclerotization around spiracles, go = genital opening, pp = posterior plate, re = receptaculum." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566383" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">4G</figureCitation>
) (concave margin on posterior plate, weak sclerotization around spiracles in 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. juchuy" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" rank="species" species="juchuy">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">N. juchuy</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanchez-Ruiz, A" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" pagination="461 - 486" refId="B6" refString="Sanchez-Ruiz, A, Brescovit, AD, Bonaldo, AB, 2020. Revision of the spider genus Nyetnops Platnick &amp; Lise (Araneae: Caponiidae) with proposition of the new genus Nopsma, from Central and South America. Zootaxa 4751 (3): 461 - 486" title="Revision of the spider genus Nyetnops Platnick &amp; Lise (Araneae: Caponiidae) with proposition of the new genus Nopsma, from Central and South America." volume="4751" year="2020">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sánchez-Ruiz">Sanchez-Ruiz</normalizedToken>
et al. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 15I); internally with median concavity on distal margin of receptaculum (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Nopsma paya sp. nov.; A, B, E, F. male holotype; C, D, G. female paratype (IAvH-I 3796). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B Habitus, ventral view. C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, prolateral view. G. External genitalia, ventral view. H. Internal genitalia, dorsal view. Scale bars: A-D: 1.5 mm, E, F: 0.7 mm, G, H: 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: ap = anterior plate, ess = external sclerotization around spiracles, go = genital opening, pp = posterior plate, re = receptaculum." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566383" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">4H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Schematic drawing of internal female genitalia in two Nopsma species. A. Nopsma juchuy (Duperre). B. Nopsma paya sp. nov. Scale bars: A, B: 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: as = anterior tracheal spiracles, dmr = distal margin of receptaculum, ess = external sclerotization around spiracles, go = genital opening, pmr = proximal margin of receptaculum, pp = posterior plate, ps = posterior tracheal spiracles, re = receptaculum." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566386" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">7B</figureCitation>
) (straight distal margin in 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. juchuy" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" rank="species" species="juchuy">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">N. juchuy</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Schematic drawing of internal female genitalia in two Nopsma species. A. Nopsma juchuy (Duperre). B. Nopsma paya sp. nov. Scale bars: A, B: 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: as = anterior tracheal spiracles, dmr = distal margin of receptaculum, ess = external sclerotization around spiracles, go = genital opening, pmr = proximal margin of receptaculum, pp = posterior plate, ps = posterior tracheal spiracles, re = receptaculum." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566386" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">7A</figureCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanchez-Ruiz, A" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" pagination="461 - 486" refId="B6" refString="Sanchez-Ruiz, A, Brescovit, AD, Bonaldo, AB, 2020. Revision of the spider genus Nyetnops Platnick &amp; Lise (Araneae: Caponiidae) with proposition of the new genus Nopsma, from Central and South America. Zootaxa 4751 (3): 461 - 486" title="Revision of the spider genus Nyetnops Platnick &amp; Lise (Araneae: Caponiidae) with proposition of the new genus Nopsma, from Central and South America." volume="4751" year="2020">
